{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ab0b7b66-18ac-4668-b7c1-e8692ce3f0e0","content":"Two things change with MTP:\n\n1. **`--filter` → `--treenode-filter`** — MTP uses a tree-path filter syntax, not VSTest's expression language.\n2. **Syntax** — glob-style paths replace operators like `~` and `&`.\n\n**Old (VSTest / xUnit v2):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**New (MTP / xUnit v3):**\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*/**[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n**How it maps:**\n\n| VSTest concept | MTP tree-node equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` | `/**/*IntegrationTests*/**` (glob path match) |\n| `&` (AND) | implicit — path + property combine as AND |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` (trait/property in brackets) |\n\nThe tree structure is `/Assembly/Namespace.Class/Method`, so `/**/*IntegrationTests*/**` matches any test under a node whose name contains `IntegrationTests`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0771b495-8a65-4ffe-85fd-ec53f5cbd5e7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is migrating from xUnit v2 to xUnit v3 with MTP (Microsoft Testing Platform). The key differences:\n\n1. **VSTest filter syntax** (`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"`) used `&` for AND and `~` for contains.\n\n2. **MTP filter syntax** is different. With MTP enabled (`UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner=true`), `dotnet test` uses `--filter` but with MTP's own filter syntax, or you can use `--treenode-filter`.\n\nLet me think about this more carefully:\n\n\nWith xUnit v3 and MTP, the old VSTest filter syntax doesn't work directly anymore. When MTP is enabled, `--filter` gets passed through to MTP's own filtering mechanism rather than using VSTest expressions, so the syntax changes depending on whether you're in VSTest mode or MTP mode.\n\nFor xUnit v3 with MTP specifically, the `--treenode-filter` option is the way to go—it uses a hierarchical path format like `/Assembly/Namespace.Class/Method` to target tests. Trait filtering works differently in this context too, though I'm still working through the exact syntax for that. Showing the dotnet test command with the treenode filter syntax for MTP, then comparing it to the older VSTest approach with the FullyQualifiedName and Category filters.","outputTokens":1319,"requestId":"1BD2:D6A27:212C5B4:2499C36:6A03CFD9"},"id":"7e96d8e2-a2f4-452c-8896-294395238f72","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:12:18.920Z","parentId":"3de3df78-69a3-474f-9bc2-644ea68794bc"}
